column3:
#BSAYF, the music video featured in our upcoming pilot &quot;Hair Story,&quot; just dropped on Billboard! It's the first single off Roy Kinsey's album &quot;blackie.&quot; 

&quot;I wanted to give voice to me being black and feminine, and a lot of people probably wouldn’t but that’s who I am, that’s how I felt and that’s how I grew up. That’s who &quot;Blackie&quot; is. Just from the times growing up being online seeing “no blacks, no fats, no femmes,” and I’m like damn I’m all of those.  And just noticing that black femmes have saved us. They have given us a soul and given birth to so many of us. So my grandmother’s voice is on there, Jenifer Lewis’s voice is on there, James Baldwin, who to me is black and feminine, is on there.&quot; - ROY KINSEY 

BSAYF stars Saya Naomi and Mister Wallace as a spin-off to #NupitaObama. It was produced by our founder Aymar Jean Christian, who created and directed the &quot;Hair Story&quot; pilot with an amazing team of writer-performers. Catch a preview at the The Art Institute of Chicago March 30 12-1PM and the free premiere at the Chicago Cultural Center in April!
